==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Freehold
<hw>Free"hold`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Lw)</fld> <def>An
estate in real property, of inheritance (in fee simple or fee tail) or
for life; or the tenure by which such estate is held.</def>
<rj><au>Kent. Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To abate into a freehold</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Abate</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Freeholder</ent>⟦br⟧
